      <hedline>
        <hl1>BRAZIL BANK RESULTS MASK STRENGTH</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Banco do Brasil reports 49 percent decline in third-quarter earnings to 373 million reais ($200 million), but results reflect extraordinary gain year earlier, when loss provisions from foreign investments worth $270 million were reported; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Brazil's biggest bank, Banco do Brasil, reported a 49 percent decline in third-quarter earnings, to 373 million reais ($200 million), but the results reflected an extraordinary gain the year earlier, when loss provisions from foreign investments worth $270 million were reported. Without the extraordinary effect, third-quarter profit would be 64 percent higher than the year before.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich</p>
      </block>
